item.title: CVE-2020-5327|2024-09-16T20:47:30.272Z -- dell -- dell%20encryption%20enterprise
item.description: Dell Security Management Server versions prior to 10.2.10 contain a Java RMI Deserialization of Untrusted Data vulnerability. When the server is exposed to the internet and Windows Firewall is disabled, a remote unauthenticated attacker may exploit this vulnerability by sending a crafted RMI request to execute arbitrary code on the target host.
